import{_ as t,o,c as a,a as r,d as e,e as n,b as s}from"./app-a6eacc5a.js";const i={},d=e("h1",{id:"why-your-life-needs-novelty-no-matter-your-age-1",tabindex:"-1"},[e("a",{class:"header-anchor",href:"#why-your-life-needs-novelty-no-matter-your-age-1","aria-hidden":"true"},"#"),n(" Why Your Life Needs Novelty, No Matter Your Age (1)")],-1),b=s('<p>In 2018, I had what I call a powerful first experience.<br> At 31 years old,<br> I made my first snow angel.<br> Now, that may not sound powerful to some of you,<br> but for me, it was.<br> And so how do you get from New York City to Montana?<br> Well, you have to have a horse.<br> I don&#39;t make the rules,<br> but not having a horse is why so many people don&#39;t <em>make it out</em> there.<br> I&#39;m kidding.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 2018 年，我有了一个震撼的第一次。<br> 在我 31 岁的时候，<br> 我第一次做了雪天使图案。<br> 也许这对有些人来说没什么大不了的，<br> 但对我来说，意义重大。<br> 你怎么从纽约去蒙大拿？<br> 好吧，你得先有匹马。<br> 这可不是我乱编的，<br> 但没有马正是很多人去不了那里的原因。<br> 开个玩笑。</p></details><p>I was actually invited to attend and speak at a <code>conference</code> in Big Sky.<br> I&#39;m a kid from the Bronx, so I knew nothing about Big Sky.<br> I knew nothing about Montana.<br> In fact, I had only recognized images similar to it as the <em>screen saver</em> that comes on whenever my MacBook <em>goes <code>idle</code></em>.<br> I landed in Bozeman and the first thing I did was thank God,<br> because I don&#39;t like flying, <em>even though</em> I have to do it often.<br> I walked out of the airport and I saw no skyscrapers,<br> no lines and <code>cabs</code>,<br> no people <code>yelling</code> and <code>arguing</code>,<br> and there were no <em>funny smells</em> that I was familiar with.<br> You know, all of the things that make NYC amazing.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 我曾受邀参与一场位于大天空市（Big Sky）的会议并发言，<br> 我是个来自纽约布朗克斯区的小孩，所以我对大天空一无所知。<br> 我对蒙大拿州一无所知。<br> 其实我只在我的苹果电脑空闲时跳出来的屏保上看到过类似的图片。<br> 我落地博兹曼市（Bozeman）后，做的第一件事就是感谢上帝，<br> 因为我不喜欢乘飞机，虽然我总是得乘飞机。<br> 我走出机场，没有看到摩天大楼，<br> 没有地铁、出租车，<br> 没有大声争吵、大喊大叫的人，<br> 也没有我熟悉的怪味。<br> 没有纽约的这些神奇之处。</p></details><p>So fast forward,<br> I&#39;m in the <em>passenger seat</em> of the car and I&#39;m looking out the window<br> and I&#39;m just <em>taking on</em> the views.<br> Mountains covered in snow, trees everywhere.<br> And <em>at one point</em> we <em>pass by</em> these homes that had to be worth millions of dollars<br> because they had the most beautiful view of the environment.<br> Later the next day, as I&#39;m <em>getting off</em> stage from speaking,<br> a woman <em>comes up</em> to me and she asks,<br> &quot;Would you like to go on a <code>hike</code>?&quot;<br> Now I’m from New York City, so a hike is a few <em>city blocks</em>.<br> New York City is at sea level, so we&#39;re talking about real oxygen.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 再然后，<br> 我坐在汽车的后排，看着窗外，<br> 真的就是在充分欣赏美景。<br> 山上覆盖着白雪，树木丛生。<br> 某一刻，我们途径了一些“价值连城”的房子，<br> 因为它们坐拥最美的风景。<br> 第二天，我发完言走下台后，<br> 一位女士走到我面前，问：<br> “你想不想来个徒步旅行？”<br> 我来自纽约，所以徒步旅行对我而言顶多是走几个街区。<br> 纽约地处海平面，所以我们现在是真有氧气。</p></details><p>So, no, this was a hike.<br> And at 8,000 <code>feet</code> elevation,<br> one quickly realizes Montana&#39;s oxygen just isn&#39;t real.<br> Midway through our hike, I can&#39;t remember what I said,<br> but the woman grabs a <code>fistful</code> of snow,<br> puts it in her mouth and she starts to <code>chew</code>.<br> And my initial thought was, &quot;That was <code>disgusting</code>.&quot;<br> I would never touch anything that touches a New York City street.<br> But then I realized this was snow from Montana,<br> and this was <code>symbolic</code> of the relationships Montanans have with their environment.<br> So <code>towards</code> the end of the hike,<br> this woman lays down in a bed of snow<br> and she moves her body in a way where [it] registers to me,<br> she&#39;s making a snow angel.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 不，这可是场徒步旅行。<br> 等你到了海拔 8000 英尺，<br> 你就知道蒙大拿可不是真有氧气。<br> 徒步途中，我不记得我说了些什么，<br> 但这位女士抓起了一捧雪，<br> 放进了嘴里，开始咀嚼。<br> 我的第一反应是：“太恶心了吧。”<br> 我可不想碰任何碰过纽约路面的东西。<br> 但我突然意识到这是蒙大拿的雪啊，<br> 这是蒙大拿人和环境之间关系的象征。<br> 徒步末尾，<br> 这位女士躺在了雪地上，<br> 她用身体做出了这样的动作，我想起来了，<br> 她在做“雪天使”啊。</p></details>',8);function m(h,l){return o(),a("div",null,[d,r(" 为什么你的生活需要新奇，无论你的年龄（1）  "),b])}const u=t(i,[["render",m],["__file","19-needs-novelty-1.html.vue"]]);export{u as default};
